{ Yuriy Krykun suggests this interesting counterstrike, and I have to say that White has to be well booked up if they want to fight properly for an advantage against quite a surprising and attractive suggestion by Black! Black could also go for the tame  5...exf4  , but that allows White to gain full central control after  6.Bxf4  c6  when Black wants to play d5 and disturb White's coordination while the King is still in the center, but after  7.d4  +/=, White is slightly better as he managed to build the center and pushed the Black pieces back.  Instead, Black can play and  5...Nc6  . Trying to develop the pieces while remaining flexible in the center, but the downside is that c6–d5 is no longer possible.  6.Nf3  White puts more pressure on the  e5  pawn in an attempt to force Black's  d6  , with a plan of f5–Bg5–Qd2 and O-O-O White will be able to start a powerful Kingside attack! }
