{ Black could also go for activation of another Rook with  13...Ra6  14.Nd2  +/  = but that does not change White's plan of Nd2 followed with a center break of d4 and c4! }
14. Bh4
{ Black has no active options and thus White can afford such a 'slow' move. The idea is to have Bg3 at hand, when and if needed, but not to drop the pin against Nf6 too soon. }
14... Ra6 15. Nd2
{ Utilizing the fact that Black's Knight is on d7 instead of c6, White gets ready to play d4 and meet Black's e4 with the immediate c4-blow. This central break would put pressure on Black's vulnerable center and White will activate pieces as it was shown in the games Model game: Yu, Y-Wang Shenzhen 2016 & Lu, S-Bai CHN-CHT 2017 }
