{ This is a committal, but necessary measure to prevent Nf5 for the time being. The drawback is that the dark-squares are now horribly weakened. If Black instead plays:   10...Bg4  White switches to the preparation of f4 with  11.Qe1  making Bishop on g4 clumsy, and after  11...Be6  12.Nhf5  Ne8  13.Nxd6  Nxd6  White finally reaches a goal with  14.f4  . Black could continue with a trade of the light-squared Bishops with  14...Bxb3  15.axb3  f6  16.Nh5  when White then prepares to attack the vulnerable g7-square with Qg3. After  16...Qc7  17.Qg3  Kh8  18.fxe5  fxe5  19.Bg5  White is slightly better with a strong threat of Nf6 and full control over the f-file. To get familiar with ideas here I would recommend you to check the game Sudnitsyn, A-Bobykin, K ICCF email 2014. }
11. Bg5
{ Development is almost done, and Black needs to think how to take back control over dark-squares which are obviously weakened. }
11... Na5
{ With this move Black obviously wants to remove the Bishop from b3. However, White will now be able to quickly open the f-file. }
12. h3
{ Before the advance of f4, we want to make sure that Black will have no possible counterplay on the Kingside with optional Bg4 or even Ng4 in some cases. White is now fully prepared for the opening of the f-file and Black can not stop it! }
12... Nxb3 13. axb3
{ It is the fact that White lost a light-squared Bishop as an important asset for the Kingside attack, but at the same time, he gained an open a-file for the Rook which now pressures the a7 spot. }
13... Be7 14. f4
{ There is no reason for White to change the plan and not to proceed with f4 and activation of the Rook on f1 and Bishop on g5. }
14... Nd7
{ Black is forced to support the e5 pawn and not to allow the opening of the f-file. At this point, it would not be very nice for White to play fxe5 when Black would gain an outpost on e5. }
15. Bxe7 Qxe7 16. Qg4
{ After a trade of Bishops, White joins the game with a Queen and threatens both Nf5 and f5 as it could be seen in a game Bajt, D-Kouba, P ICCF email 2013. White has at least a slight advantage, with a further plan of the Kingside attack, possible doubling of Rooks on the f-file, and activating Knights. }
