{ Like in many instances when the Black Knight is on d7, White uses development advantage to harass Black's central pawns! }
7... Nxd5
{ This is considered a suspcious move by Black since White can immediately strike in the center now! }
8. d4 e4
{ If Black instead went for development with  8...O-O  9.Bg5!  would provoke the weakening with f6, and White would follow with Bh4–Bg3, Re1 with huge initiative and activity. }
9. Ng5
{ It is an early stage and Black is already over-extended. The pawn on e4 is hanging and White has tactics with Nf7-c4-c5 at his disposal. }
9... N7f6
{ Have in mind that Black can not go for  9...f5?!  due to  10.c4  and huge advantage due to the forthcoming c5! }
10. c4
{ And with the previously mentioned idea of Nxf7 followed by a discovered check with c5, White reaches a clearly better position. }
