{ This is a very common move by Black, who tends to develop the Kingside as soon as possible. Threatening the f2 pawn, Black might also choose to continue afterward with the tricky Qf6. Anyway, 3...Bc5?! is suspicious since g7 becomes vulnerable! I would like to point out that lots of weaker players go for it since it resembles the Italian Guicco Piano, and a majority of the players that like to do it hope that it is the same or at least very similar to it. Still, luckily for us, it is not! }
