{ Although Black hopes to kick out the annoying dark-squared Bishop, that ain't going to be easy! }
10. Qh4
{ White keeps the choke on Black's pieces and defends the piece with the most active move, which comes with a threat on the Knight on f6! Black is forced to search for any tactical engagements to save the piece, but it is pretty much late, and White gains a decisive advantage! }
10... Ng4
{ With a motive of Bxf2 in mind, Black hopes to win those exchanges on that end without any material loss. }
11. Bxe6
{ This is a very important intermediary move that guarantees a winning position to White as it will be shown within a few moves! }
11... Bxf2+ 12. Qxf2 Nxf2 13. Bxd8 Nxh1 14. Bf6
{ These beautiful tactical motives could be seen in a Rapid game between Mamedyarov, S-Amin, B INT Rapid 2020 where White gains a decisive material advantage of two Bishops for a Rook. Despite that, Black's Knight on h1 has no space to move away, and the game is practically over after only 14 moves! }
