{ Black needs to decide now what to do with the center. White attacks the e5 pawn and threatens to play 10.exd5 with the forthcoming c4 and Bb2! Black is practically forced to open the position up with 9...dxe4. }
9... dxe4
{ If you have wondered how should White react if Black went for  9...Bg4  , I would say that in that case, White gains a clear advantage after  10.h3  forcing Black to take  10...Bxf3  and after  11.Qxf3  White threatens 12.Ba3 Black cannot castle anymore! }
10. Nxe5
{ White improves the position of the Knight, overtakes the center from Black, and has a simple idea of further development with Bg5, Re1, d4 establishing control in the center and making Black's pawn on e4 exposed to attacks. }
10... O-O
{ Naturally Black goes for castling, and we keep our original idea to follow-up with Bg5! }
11. Bg5
{ Transposes to 5...Bb4 6.Nf3 Nxb3 7.axb3 O-O 8. O-O d5 9.Bg5! Bxc3 10.bxc3 dxe4 11.Ne5 }
