7. f5
{ I enjoy this move and concept a lot in the Bishop's opening! White limits the scope of Black's pieces @@StartBracket@@mainly Bc8@@EndBracket@@ and opens the way for the dark-squared Bishop which would be very uncomfortable for Black after Bg5 and the idea of Nd5.   Instead of 7.f5! the interesting move  7.Na4!?  gives a slight advantage to White thanks to the Bishop pair that White will gain later on. }
