12. Bb3
{ With full control of dark squares and a target on the f7, White is at least slightly better without problems in development. The pawn on c2 is defended and White has the better piece activity, whilst Black needs to think about the King's safety and marginalized Knight on h5 which does not have lots of possibilities for activation. I had this position a few times in the practice and it is full of interesting possibilities but not easy at all for playing. White has better chances, but do not overestimate yours and underestimate their chances! }
