10... Nh5
{ This move was played in a game Pichushkin, V-Nadeev, S ICCF email 2012 where Black aimed to protect g7 to be able to continue with Nc2. }
11. Qg4
{ White uses the opportunity to remove the Knight from h5 and does not have fears about Nc2, because as it was shown earlier, Black's Knight on a1 will be trapped after taking the Rook. }
11... Nxc2+ 12. Kd1 Nxa1 13. Qxh5
