6... Qf6
{ One may think that it is a good decision for Black to try to exchange pieces as soon as possible and to escape from an attack, but that ain't gonna work easily. }
7. Re1+
{ Once again we develop with a check, putting Black into the uncomfortable pin and at the same time, we delay the decision whether we are going to exchange Queens or not. }
7... Be7 8. Qd1
{ With much better development and the active threat of Bg5, we choose not to exchange Queens and simply go back to the starting square where the Queen can not be exposed to any attacks. Besides the obvious threat of Bg5, White wants to continue with Qe2, stopping Black to castle and finally Nc3- followed by Nd5. White is much better and with Black's miserable pieces placed on the back rank, Black can only dream about striking back. }
