8... Kf8
{ Although this move may look illogical, it can be dangerous. Black aims to activate pieces through the g-file eyeing our King on g1. However, this will not end up that way, as you will see soon! }
9. Nbd2
{ Whenever you have a chance to develop with a tempo attack - you should do it! An active development move buys time for future actions. Not only that Black's pawn on c4 hangs, but we want to centralize and cover important dark squares after the forthcoming Ne4! }
9... gxf6
{ There are many ways for Black to directly enter the losing position and this is only one of them. It looks that Black does not have issues with dark squares at this moment, but this is only temporary. }
10. Ne4
{ Following the mentioned idea we put Black into trouble! 11.Bh6 will follow with a tremendous attack after 12.Qd2 and Black will be left without useful moves! }
10... Be7
{ Black desperately tries to cover the dark squares, but it is too late... }
11. Bh6+
{ Another tempo development move for White, leading to a deadly attack. Black's King will be locked to g8 and it is obvious that we will have a bunch of mating threats through the g7 square. }
11... Kg8 12. Qd2
{ It can be already said that White has a huge advantage. King on g8 is in the mating net and White aims to finish the game with the Qf4-Qg3 idea. Of course, Black also faces issues with terrible pawn structure and f6 and d4 weaknesses. There are many ideas for the following development and I would turn to some of them.   It maybe looks that Black covers the King with  12...Ne5  but after  13.Qf4  Black again faces issues of mate threats. The only defending move would be  13...Ng6  there, but White strikes back with beautiful tactical engagement  14.Nxf6!  Black needs to accept the sacrifice  14...Bxf6  15.Qxf6!  but White does not stop and again threatens to mate with Qg7. Of course after  15...Qxf6  16.Re8  comes with an unstoppable mate  16...Nf8  17.Rxf8#   If instead, Black tries to cover the King with  12...Bf5  White is clearly winning after  13.Qf4  ,  threatening the Bishop and forcing  13...Bg6  Once again, beautiful tactics decide the result  14.Nxf6!  Bxf6  and Black cannot stop  15.Re8!  Qxe8  with  16.Qxf6  coming afterward with a scary Qg7 mate threat. }
