11. Nce4
{ Once again we improve the position of our pieces with a tempo attack. Do not be naive to trust that our idea is only to take  11....--  12.Nxc5  with following 13. Ne6,   but we have a cunning threat of  11...--  12.fxg7  with 13. g4! This would put Black's Queen into trouble since the Qf5 won't be able to hold both f6 and Bc5. }
11... O-O
{ Kingside castling is not a good idea for Black. It maybe looks that Black's King will find safe spots and that Qf5 holds most of the squares there. It will be shown that is not easy as it sounds for Black to hold the position here. }
12. fxg7
{ White starts to break the Kingside and all of a sudden we get a bunch of opportunities for further activation and mate attacks. Following a few more moves, Black will face troubles that would force him to resign! }
12... Kxg7
{ Do not forget that whenever Black's King stays on the g8 square, for example after  12...Rfe8  , White has a fierce answer  13.g4!  Black's Queen will once again be stretched to defense of both f6 square and the Bishop on c5, and it is impossible to take care of both of them! }
13. Nxc5
{ I think that it is already obvious that King on g7 and Queen on c5 would be available for sacrifices and forks. This is our main goal that will be achieved very soon! }
13... Qxc5 14. Rxe6
{ Since Black cannot recapture with  14...fxe6  due to the double attack  15.Nxe6  ,  Black ends up here with a piece down and a weakened King. }
